px |title=MAC Announces 2018 Football Schedule |publisher=Mid-American Conference |date=February 22, 2018 |accessdate=February 22, 2018}}</ref> The [[2018 MAC Championship Game|MAC Championship Game]] will be held on November 30, 2018.\n\n==Previous season==\n{{main|2017 Mid-American Conference football season}}In [[2017 NCAA Division I FBS football season|2017]], [[2017 Akron Zips football team|Akron]] won the East Division with a 6\u20132 conference record while [[2017 Toledo Rockets football team|Toledo]] won the West Division with a 7\u20131 conference record. Toledo defeated Akron in the [[2017 MAC Championship Game|MAC Championship game]].\n\n==Preseason==\n\n===Preseason Poll===\nThe MAC Preseason Media Poll was released at the MAC Media Day on July 24, 2018 in [[Detroit|Detroit, Michigan]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://getsomemaction.com/news/2018/7/23/niu-ohio-picked-as-divisional-winners-in-2018-mac-football-media-preseason-poll.aspx|title=NIU & Ohio Picked As Divisional Winners In 2018 MAC Football Media Preseason Poll|access-date=2018-07-24|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==== East ====\n\n#[[2018 Ohio Bobcats football team|Ohio]] ''(21)''\n#[[2018 Buffalo Bulls football team|Buffalo]] ''(1)''\n#[[2018 Miami RedHawks football team|Miami]] ''(2)''\n#[[2018 Akron Zips football team|Akron]]\n#[[2018 Bowling Green Falcons football team|Bowling Green]]\n#[[2018 Kent State Golden Flashes football team|Kent State]]\n\n==== West ====\n\n#[[2018 Northern Illinois Huskies football team|Northern Illinois]] ''(15)''\n#[[2018 Toledo Rockets football team|Toledo]] ''(7)''\n#[[2018 Western Michigan Broncos football team|Western Michigan]] ''(1)''\n#[[2018 Eastern Michigan Eagles football team|Eastern Michigan]] \n#[[2018 Central Michigan Chippewas football team|Central Michigan]] ''(1)''\n#[[2018 Ball State Cardinals football team|Ball State]]\n\n''(first place votes)''\n\n==== MAC Championship ====\nOhio received 13 votes as the predicted 2018 MAC Championship Game winner. Toledo (5), Northern Illinois (4), Miami (1), and Central Michigan (1) also received votes.\n\n==Head coaches==\n\n=== Coaching changes ===\nOn November 22, 2018, one day after [[2017 Kent State Golden Flashes football team|Kent State]]'s final game of the season against [[Akron Zips football|Akron]], the school fired head coach [[Paul Haynes (American football)|Paul Haynes]] after five losing seasons.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.espn.com/college-football/story/_/id/21517111/kent-state-fires-football-coach-paul-haynes-5-losing-seasons|title=Kent State fires Haynes after 5 losing seasons|work=ESPN.com|access-date=2018-01-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.ohio.com/akron/sports/kent-state-reportedly-fires-football-coach-after-loss-to-akron|title=Kent State fires football coach Paul Haynes after loss to Akron|last=rlewis|work=www.ohio.com|access-date=2018-01-16|language=en-US}}</ref> On December 19, the school hired [[Sean Lewis (American football)|Sean Lewis]] as head coach.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.record-courier.com/sports/20171218/kent-state-hires-sean-lewis-as-new-football-coach|title=Kent State hires Sean Lewis as new football coach|last=Writer|first=Allen Moff Staff|work=Record|access-date=2018-01-16|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cleveland.com/sports/college/index.ssf/2017/12/syracuse_sean_lewis_anticipate.html|title=Syracuse's Sean Lewis to be named Kent State's new head football coach|work=cleveland.com|access-date=2018-01-16|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n=== Coaches ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center;font-size:90%;\"\n|-\n! width=\"110\" | Team\n! Head coach\n! Previous job\n! Years at school\n! Overall record\n! MAC record\n! MAC titles\n|-\n!style={{NCAA color cell|Akron Zips}}|Akron\n| [[Terry Bowden]]\n|[[North Alabama Lions football|North Alabama]]\n|7\n|{{winning percentage|31|44|record=y}}\n|{{winning percentage|21|27|record=y}}\n|0\n|-\n!style={{NCAA color cell|Ball State Cardinals}}|Ball State