ulien\n|Eastern Michigan\n|}\n\n====Week Fourteen====\n{{CFB Conference Schedule Start}}\n{{CFB Conference Schedule Entry\n| w/l           = l\n| date          = December 1\n| time          = 12:00 p.m.\n| visiting_team = '''Akron'''\n| home_team     = [[2018 South Carolina Gamecocks football team|South Carolina]]\n| site_stadium = [[Williams\u2013Brice Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Columbia, South Carolina|Columbia, SC]]\n| tv = SECN\n| score         = 3\u201328\n| attend        = 53,420\n}}\n{{CFB Conference Schedule End|timezone=[[Eastern Time Zone|Eastern Time]]}}\nThis game was added after Akron's game vs Nebraska was cancelled due to lightning and South Carolina's game vs Marshall was cancelled due to [[Hurricane Florence]].\n\n====MAC Championship Game====\n{{See also|2018 MAC Championship Game}}\n{{CFB Conference Schedule Start}}\n{{CFB Conference Schedule Entry\n| w/l           = \n| date          = {{tooltip|November 30|Friday}}\n| time          = 7:00 p.m.\n| visiting_team = Northern Illinois\n| home_team     = Buffalo\n| site_stadium = [[Ford Field]]\n| site_cityst = [[Detroit|Detroit, MI]]\n| tv = ESPN2\n| score         = '''NIU''' 30\u201329\n| attend        = 10,255\n}}\n{{CFB Conference Schedule End|timezone=[[Mountain Time Zone|Mountain Time]]}}\n\n==Postseason==\n===Bowl games===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%\"\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Legend\n|-\n| style=\"background:#bfb;\"|&nbsp;||MAC win\n|-\n| style=\"background:#fbb;\"|&nbsp;||MAC loss\n|}\n\n{{See also|2018\u201319 NCAA football bowl games}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-'''Bowl games'''\n!Bowl game\n!Date\n!Site\n!Television\n!Time ([[Eastern Time Zone|EST]])\n!MAC team\n!Opponent\n!Score\n!Attendance\n|-style=\"background:#fbb;\"\n|[[2018 Camellia Bowl|Camellia Bowl]]\n|December 15\n|[[Cramton Bowl]] \u2022 [[Montgomery, Alabama|Montgomery, AL]]\n|[[ESPN College Football|ESPN]]\n|5:30 p.m.\n|[[2018 Eastern Michigan Eagles football team|Eastern Michigan]]\n|[[2018 Georgia Souther