04\n|43.3%\n|-\n!style=\"background:#00694E; color:white;\"|Ohio\n|[[Peden Stadium]]\n|24,000\n|18,275\n|19,056\n|19,492 \u2020\n|13,774\n|13,839\n|12,938\n| style=\"background:#666666;\" |\n|97,374\n|16,229\n|67.6%\n|-\n!style=\"background:#002569; color:#FFCE00;\"|Toledo\n|[[Glass Bowl]]\n|26,248\n|24,136\n|'''28,117''' \u2020\n|23,675\n|24,685\n|18,114\n|15,214\n|15,521\n|124,777\n|17,825\n|67.9%\n|-\n!style=\"background:#442416; color:#FFAE00;\"|Western Michigan\n|[[Waldo Stadium]]\n|30,200\n|20,628\n|23,244\n|24,282 \u2020\n|11,389\n|11,935\n|18,278\n| style=\"background:#666666;\" |\n|98,021\n|16,337\n|54.1%\n|-\n|}\n'''Bold''' \u2013 Exceed capacity<br/>\n\u2020Season High\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Mid-American Conference football navbox}}\n{{2018 NCAA Division I FBS football season navbox}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2018 Mid-American Conference football season}}\n[[Category:2018 Mid-American Conference football season|*]]\n", "name_user": "Joeykai", "label": "safe", "comment": "linkNathan RourkeusingFind link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2018_Mid-American_Conference_football_season"}
{"title_page": "Lisa Nicole Carson", "text_new": "{{short description|American actress|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Lisa Nicole Carson\n| image = \n| imagesize = \n| caption = \n| birth_name = \n| birth_date ={{Birth date and age|1969|7|12}}\n| birth_place = [[Brooklyn, New York]], U.S.\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| othername = \n| occupation = Actress\n| years_active = 1991\u2013present\n| spouse = \n| partner = \n| website = \n}}\n\n'''Lisa Nicole Carson''' (born July 12, 1969) is an American actress. She is known for her work on U.S. television, including supporting roles in [[NBC]]'s ''[[ER (TV series)|ER]]'' and [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]]'s ''[[Ally McBeal]]''. Carson appeared in the roles simultaneously, but afterwards, she withdrew from acting<ref>{{cite news|author=Vivan, Rhiannon|url= https://www.mirror.co.uk/celebs-old/celebs-on-sunday/features/2008/02/24/calista-flockhart-i-have-zero-ambition-115875-20324817/|title= Calista Flockhart: I have zero ambition|newspaper=[[Daily Mirror|The Mirror]] |date=2008-02-24| accessdate=2009-02-19}}</ref> until 2012 when she appeared in the final episode of [[David E. Kelley]]'s ''[[Harry's Law]]''.\n\n==Early life==\nCarson was born in [[Brooklyn, New York]]; her father is a journalism professor at the [[University of Florida]], and her mother was a kindergarten teacher in New York.<ref name=\"interview\">{{cite magazine|url= http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m1355/is_n19_v94/ai_21250383?tag=content;col1|title= Lisa Nicole Carson brings sex appeal and excitement to tv and movies|magazine=Jet  | date = 1998-10-05| accessdate=2008-08-17}}{{dead link|date=October 2013}}</ref> She spent her adolescence in [[Gainesville, Florida]] and attended [[Buchholz High School|F. W. Buchholz High School]]. Her parents separated when she was 14, and her mother moved back to New York alone.<ref name=\"interview\"/> In 1986, she entered the Regional competition sponsored by the \"America's Junior Miss\" talent show, taking second place for the region held in Gainesville. After graduating in 1987, Carson returned to New York and decided that she wanted to be an actor. She began her career by appearing in a number of [[After School Special]]s and [[Home Box Office|HBO]] short films.\n\n==Career==\nCarson appeared in productions at the famed Negro Ensemble Company. Her first notable credit came in 1991, when she appeared in ''[[Law & Order]]'' and in 1992 she had a non-speaking, minor role in the comedy series, ''[[The Cosby Show]]''.<ref>[https://archive.is/20120919084933/http://www.usaweekend.com/98_issues/980517/980517straight_talk_carson.html Lisa Nicole Carson]</ref> She was a regular on ''The Apollo Comedy Hour'' before appearing in film in ''Let's Get Bizzee'' (1993), ''[[Jason's Lyric]]'' (1994) and ''[[Devil in a Blue Dress (film)|Devil in a Blue Dress]]'' (1995). She has appeared in ''[[Love Jones (film)|Love Jones]]'' and ''[[Life (1999 film)|Life]]''. She also performed as an R&B singer in the 1995 television movie ''Divas''. She had a role in the 1997 movie ''[[Eve's Bayou]]'', as Mattie Mereaux.\n\nOn television, she played the recurring character Carla Reece, the on/off girlfriend of [[Eriq La Salle]]'s Dr [[Peter Benton]] in NBC's ''ER'' between 1996 and 2001. Between 1997 and 2002 she played prose hviyfuyfutchc hub h vcjgcujgxckyrsyrfx hfcx5dc tcd7tcg jgctc hg gcutor Renee Raddick in Fox's ''[[Ally McBeal]]'', a role for which she received multiple award nominations. Carson was fired from both roles, amid reports about her erratic behavior on and off set, alleged drug use, being arrested and admissions to a mental health facility.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://clutchmagonline.com/lifeculture/feature/what-happened-to-lisa-nicole-carson/#1|title=What Happened to Lisa Nicole Carson?|work=[[Clutch Magazine]]|accessdate=28 December 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110408151203/http://clutchmagonline.com/lifeculture/feature/what-happened-to-lisa-nicole-carson/#1|archive-date=2011-04-08|url-status=dead}}</ref> In 2012, she was featured in a guest appearance in the second-season finale of the canceled NBC series ''[[Harry's Law]]'' reprising her character Renee Raddick from ''Ally McBeal''.<ref>https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0004808/</ref>\n\nIn 2017, she starred in the [[BET]] miniseries ''[[The New Edition Story]]''.\n\n==Personal life==\nIn 2000, she was arrested for 'interfering with a lawful business establishment' and 'not leaving the premises' after a disorderly conduct incident at a luxury hotel.<ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.questia.com/read/1G1-63530166|title= THE CURSE OF TV SUCCESS|newspaper=The Birmingham Post   | accessdate=2008-08-17}}</ref>\n\nIn the July 2015 issue of ''[[Essence (magazine)|Essence]]'', Carson gave an interview in which she openly described her struggles with [[bipolar disorder]] and how the illness has affected her life and career. After having taken a 10-year hiatus from show business to live and receive treatment in New York, she reported having moved back to Los Angeles with plans to revitalize her acting career.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.essence.com/2015/06/09/woman-interrupted-lisa-nicole-carson-opens-about-her-struggle-bipolar-disorder|title= Woman, Interrupted: Lisa Nicole Carson Opens Up About her Struggle With Bipolar Disorder|publisher=ESSENCE  | accessdate=2015-07-19}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|id=0004808|name=Lisa Nicole Carson}}\n\n{{ScreenActorsGuildAwards EnsembleTVComedy 1994\u20131999}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Carson, Lisa Nicole}}\n[[Category:1969 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Actresses from New York City]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:Buchholz High School alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Brooklyn]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Gainesville, Florida]]\n[[Category:African-American actresses]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:20th-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:People with bipolar disorder]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American actress|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Lisa Nicole Carson\n| image = \n| imagesize = \n| caption = \n| birth_name = \n| birth_date ={{Birth date and age|1969|7|12}}\n| birth_place = [[Brooklyn, New York]], U.S.\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| othername = \n| occupation = Actress\n| years_active = 1991\u2013present\n| spouse = \n| partner = \n| website = \n}}\n\n'''Lisa Nicole Carson''' (born July 12, 1969) is an American actress. She is known for her work on U.S. television, including supporting roles in [[NBC]]'s ''[[ER (TV series)|ER]]'' and [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]]'s ''[[Ally McBeal]]''. Carson appeared in the roles simultaneously, but afterwards, she withdrew from acting<ref>{{cite news|author=Vivan, Rhiannon|url= https://www.mirror.co.uk/celebs-old/celebs-on-sunday/features/2008/02/24/calista-flockhart-i-have-zero-ambition-115875-20324817/|title= Calista Flockhart: I have zero ambition|newspaper=[[Daily Mirror|The Mirror]] |date=2008-02-24| accessdate=2009-02-19}}</ref> until 2012 when she appeared in the final episode of [[David E. Kelley]]'s ''[[Harry's Law]]''.\n\n==Early life==\nCarson was born in [[Brooklyn, New York]]; her father is a journalism professor at the [[University of Florida]], and her mother was a kindergarten teacher in New York.<ref name=\"interview\">{{cite magazine|url= http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m1355/is_n19_v94/ai_21250383?tag=content;col1|title= Lisa Nicole Carson brings sex appeal and excitement to tv and movies|magazine=Jet  | date = 1998-10-05| accessdate=2008-08-17}}{{dead link|date=October 2013}}</ref> She spent her adolescence in [[Gainesville, Florida]] and attended [[Buchholz High School|F. W. Buchholz High School]]. Her parents separated when she was 14, and her mother moved back to New York alone.<ref name=\"interview\"/> In 1986, she entered the Regional competition sponsored by the \"America's Junior Miss\" talent show, taking second place for the region held in Gainesville. After graduating in 1987, Carson returned to New York and decided that she wanted to be an actor. She began her career by appearing in a number of [[After School Special]]s and [[Home Box Office|HBO]] short films.\n\n==Career==\nCarson appeared in productions at the famed Negro Ensemble Company. Her first notable credit came in 1991, when she appeared in ''[[Law & Order]]'' and in 1992 she had a non-speaking, minor role in the comedy series, ''[[The Cosby Show]]''.<ref>[https://archive.is/20120919084933/http://www.usaweekend.com/98_issues/980517/980517straight_talk_carson.html Lisa Nicole Carson]</ref> She was a regular on ''The Apollo Comedy Hour'' before appearing in film in ''Let's Get Bizzee'' (1993), ''[[Jason's Lyric]]'' (1994) and ''[[Devil in a Blue Dress (film)|Devil in a Blue Dress]]'' (1995). She has appeared in ''[[Love Jones (film)|Love Jones]]'' and ''[[Life (1999 film)|Life]]''. She also performed as an R&B singer in the 1995 television movie ''Divas''. She had a role in the 1997 movie ''[[Eve's Bayou]]'', as Mattie Mereaux.\n\nOn television, she played the recurring character Carla Reece, the on/off girlfriend of [[Eriq La Salle]]'s Dr [[Peter Benton]] in NBC's ''ER'' between 1996 and 2001. Between 1997 and 2002 she played prosecutor Renee Raddick in Fox's ''[[Ally McBeal]]'', a role for which she received multiple award nominations. Carson was fired from both roles, amid reports about her erratic behavior on and off set, alleged drug use, being arrested and admissions to a mental health facility.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://clutchmagonline.com/lifeculture/feature/what-happened-to-lisa-nicole-carson/#1|title=What Happened to Lisa Nicole Carson?|work=[[Clutch Magazine]]|accessdate=28 December 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110408151203/http://clutchmagonline.com/lifeculture/feature/what-happened-to-lisa-nicole-carson/#1|archive-date=2011-04-08|url-status=dead}}</ref> In 2012, she was featured in a guest appearance in the second-season finale of the canceled NBC series ''[[Harry's Law]]'' reprising her character Renee Raddick from ''Ally McBeal''.<ref>https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0004808/</ref>\n\nIn 2017, she starred in the [[BET]] miniseries ''[[The New Edition Story]]''.\n\n==Personal life==\nIn 2000, she was arrested for 'interfering with a lawful business establishment' and 'not leaving the premises' after a disorderly conduct incident at a luxury hotel.<ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.questia.com/read/1G1-63530166|title= THE CURSE OF TV SUCCESS|newspaper=The Birmingham Post   | accessdate=2008-08-17}}</ref>\n\nIn the July 2015 issue of ''[[Essence (magazine)|Essence]]'', Carson gave an interview in which she openly described her struggles with [[bipolar disorder]] and how the illness has affected her life and career. After having taken a 10-year hiatus from show business to live and receive treatment in New York, she reported having moved back to Los Angeles with plans to revitalize her acting career.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.essence.com/2015/06/09/woman-interrupted-lisa-nicole-carson-opens-about-her-struggle-bipolar-disorder|title= Woman, Interrupted: Lisa Nicole Carson Opens Up About her Struggle With Bipolar Disorder|publisher=ESSENCE  | accessdate=2015-07-19}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|id=0004808|name=Lisa Nicole Carson}}\n\n{{ScreenActorsGuildAwards EnsembleTVComedy 1994\u20131999}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Carson, Lisa Nicole}}\n[[Category:1969 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Actresses from New York City]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:Buchholz High School alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Brooklyn]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Gainesville, Florida]]\n[[Category:African-American actresses]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\